This paper is about spoken language understanding (SLU) in task-oriented dialogue systems, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which covers NLP and related topics. The paper also proposes a neural network-based approach, which suggests that it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the trade-offs between accuracy and computational efficiency, which could be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.SD (Software Engineering) or cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
